phical turn the grounds for a mature renewal of metaphysics. Possenti takes the reader on a "third voyage" that goes beyond the "second voyage" indicated by Plato in the Phaedo. He traces the ascendancy of nihilism in philosophy, offering critical examinations of Nietzsche, Gentile, Heidegger, Habermas, Husserl, Gadamer, Ricoeur, and Vattimo. With penetrating accounts of philosophical movements such as hermeneutics and logical empiricism, rich with both historical and theoretical insights, Possenti provides a compelling defense of the power of human reason to apprehend the most obvious but also the most profound aspect of things: that they exist. By exploring the ubiquity of nihilism and probing its philosophical roots, Possenti clears the way for a fresh reformulation of metaphysics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aKnowledge, Theory of -- History -- 19th century. 0aKnowledge, Theory of -- History -- 20th century. 0aKnowledge, Theory ofxHistoryy19th century. 0aKnowledge, Theory ofxHistoryy20th century. 0aMetaphysics -- History -- 19th century. 0aMetaphysics -- History -- 20th century. 0aMetaphysicsxHistoryy19th century. 0aMetaphysicsxHistoryy20th century. 0aNihilism (Philosophy) -- History. 0aNihilism (Philosophy)xHistory. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Hermeneutics. 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh1 aGallagher, Daniel B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHabermas, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchroeder, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845208140uhttps://w